NAIROBI, KENYA: Motorists using the Nairobi-Mombasa Highway have been warned of traffic diversion from Monday 19. Kenya National Highways Authority said it will divert all traffic along a section of the Athi River- Machakos turnoff Junction Road to facilitate the rehabilitation works currently being undertaken along the project road. ALSO READ:

Wavinya poll case verdict due February The 300m diversion will be at Mua road junction, about 3km from Kyumvu town towards Nairobi and 2km from Maanzoni Lodge towards Mombasa. “Motorists are advised to obey traffic signs, installed signals and traffic flaggers, as well as maintain low speeds along the section,” reads a notice from the Authority.